# Uses google authenticator library as PAM module using a single folder for all users tokens.
# "user=nobody" pins a fixed, existing account so the module works for virtual users that
# have no system account, while only requiring privileges to seteuid to "nobody". The OpenVPN
# server drops privileges to "user nobody" (see ovpn_genconfig), so the auth-pam background
# process must be able to read the secret as "nobody"; ovpn_otp_user chowns the tokens to match.
# See https://github.com/google/google-authenticator-libpam#usersome-user
auth required pam_google_authenticator.so secret=/etc/openvpn/otp/${USER}.google_authenticator user=nobody

# Accept any user since we're dealing with virtual users there's no need to have a system account (pam_unix.so)
account sufficient pam_permit.so
